{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Welcome to 10,000 feet."},{"time":3000,"text":"Let me explain why we are here"},{"time":4000,"text":"and why some of you have a pine cone close to you."},{"time":8000,"text":"Once upon a time, I did a book called \"How Buildings Learn.\""},{"time":11000,"text":"Today's event you might call \"How Mountains Teach.\""},{"time":15000,"text":"A little background: For 10 years I've been trying to figure out how to"},{"time":17000,"text":"hack civilization so that we can get long-term thinking"},{"time":22000,"text":"to be automatic and common instead of difficult and rare --"},{"time":26000,"text":"or in some cases, non-existent."},{"time":29000,"text":"It would be helpful if humanity got into the habit of thinking"},{"time":34000,"text":"of the now not just as next week or next quarter, but you know,"},{"time":38000,"text":"next 10,000 years and the last 10,000 years --"},{"time":42000,"text":"basically civilization's story so far."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46000,"text":"So we have the Long Now Foundation in San Francisco."},{"time":48000,"text":"It's an incubator for about a dozen projects,"},{"time":50000,"text":"all having to do with continuity over the long term."},{"time":54000,"text":"Our core project is a rather ambitious folly --"},{"time":59000,"text":"I suppose, a mythic undertaking: to build a 10,000-year clock"},{"time":64000,"text":"that can really keep good time for that long a period."},{"time":69000,"text":"And the design problems of a project like that are just absolutely delicious."},{"time":76000,"text":"Go to the clock. And what we have here is something"},{"time":81000,"text":"many of you saw here three years ago."},{"time":83000,"text":"It's the first working prototype of the clock."},{"time":85000,"text":"It's about nine feet high."},{"time":86000,"text":"Designed by Danny Hillis and Alexander Rose. It's presently in London,"},{"time":91000,"text":"and is ticking away very deliberately at the science museum there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95000,"text":"So the design problem for today is going to be,"},{"time":99000,"text":"how do you house an eventual monumental clock like this"},{"time":103000,"text":"so it can really tick, save time beautifully for 100 centuries?"},{"time":108000,"text":"Well, this was the first solution."},{"time":110000,"text":"Alexander Rose came up with this idea"},{"time":112000,"text":"of a spiraloid tower with continuous sloping ramps."},{"time":117000,"text":"And it looked like a way to go, until you start thinking"},{"time":119000,"text":"about, what does deep time do to a building?"},{"time":122000,"text":"Well, this is what deep time does to a building."},{"time":125000,"text":"This is the Parthenon. It's only 2,450 years old,"},{"time":129000,"text":"and look what happened to it."},{"time":130000,"text":"Here's a beautiful project. They really knew it'd last forever,"},{"time":133000,"text":"because they'd build it out of absolutely huge stones."},{"time":137000,"text":"And now it's a pathetic ruin and no one even knows what it was used for."},{"time":140000,"text":"That's what happens to buildings. They're vulnerable."},{"time":143000,"text":"Even the most durable and intactable buildings,"},{"time":146000,"text":"like the pyramids of Giza, are in bad shape when you look up close."},{"time":150000,"text":"They've been looted inside and out."},{"time":153000,"text":"And they're built to protect things but they don't protect things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156000,"text":"So we got to thinking, if you can't put things safely in a building,"},{"time":160000,"text":"where can you safely put them? We thought, OK, underground."},{"time":163000,"text":"How about underground with a view?"},{"time":166000,"text":"Underground in a place that's really solid."},{"time":168000,"text":"So the obvious answer was, we need a mountain."},{"time":172000,"text":"You don't want just any mountain."},{"time":174000,"text":"You need absolutely the right mountain"},{"time":177000,"text":"if you're going to have a clock for 10,000 years."},{"time":179000,"text":"So here's an image of the long view of the search problem."},{"time":184000,"text":"And we got to thinking for various reasons it ought to be a desert mountain,"},{"time":188000,"text":"so we got looking in the dry areas of the Southwest."},{"time":191000,"text":"We looked at mesas in New Mexico."},{"time":194000,"text":"We were looking at dead volcanoes in Arizona."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196000,"text":"Then Roger Kennedy, who was the director of the National Parks Service,"},{"time":199000,"text":"led us to Eastern Nevada,"},{"time":201000,"text":"to America's newest and oldest national park,"},{"time":204000,"text":"which is called Great Basin National Park."},{"time":208000,"text":"It's right on the eastern border of Nevada."},{"time":211000,"text":"It's the highest range in the state -- over 13,000 feet."},{"time":215000,"text":"And you'll notice that on the left, on the left, on the west, it's very steep,"},{"time":219000,"text":"and on the right it's gentle."},{"time":222000,"text":"This place is remote. It's over 200 miles from any major city."},{"time":226000,"text":"It's nowhere near any Interstate or railroad."},{"time":229000,"text":"And it's -- the only thing that goes by is what's called"},{"time":233000,"text":"America's loneliest highway, U.S. 50."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237000,"text":"Now, inside the yellow line here, on the right is -- that's all national park."},{"time":242000,"text":"Inside the green line is national forest."},{"time":245000,"text":"And then over to the left is Bureau of Land Management land and some private land."},{"time":249000,"text":"Now, as it happened, that two-mile-long strip right in the middle,"},{"time":252000,"text":"this vertical, was available because it was private land."},{"time":258000,"text":"And thanks to Jay Walker who was here and Mitch Kapor who was here,"},{"time":262000,"text":"who started the process, Long Now was able to get that two-mile-long strip of land."},{"time":268000,"text":"And now let's look at the grand truth of what's there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271000,"text":"We're in Pole Canyon, looking west up the western escarpment"},{"time":275000,"text":"of Mount Washington, which is 11,600 feet on top."},{"time":280000,"text":"Those white cliffs are a dense Cambrian limestone."},{"time":283000,"text":"That's a 2,000-foot thick formation,"},{"time":286000,"text":"and it might be a beautiful place to hide a clock."},{"time":291000,"text":"It would be a pilgrimage to get to it; it would be a serious hike"},{"time":294000,"text":"to get up to where the clock is."},{"time":297000,"text":"So last June, the Long Now board, some staff and some donors"},{"time":302000,"text":"and advisors, made a two-week expedition to the mountain"},{"time":307000,"text":"to explore it and investigate, one, if it's the right mountain,"},{"time":312000,"text":"and two, if it's the right mountain, how it might actually work for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316000,"text":"Now Danny Hillis sort of framed the problem."},{"time":319000,"text":"He has a theory of how the overall clock experience should work."},{"time":322000,"text":"It's what he calls the seven stages of a mythic adventure."},{"time":326000,"text":"It starts with the image. The image is a picture you have in your mind"},{"time":330000,"text":"of the goal at the end of the journey."},{"time":332000,"text":"In this case it might well be an image of the clock."},{"time":335000,"text":"Then there's the point of embarkation, that is, the point of transition"},{"time":339000,"text":"from ordinary life to being a pilgrim on a quest."},{"time":343000,"text":"Then -- this is a nice image of it, there's the labyrinth."},{"time":347000,"text":"The labyrinth is a concept, it's like a twilight zone,"},{"time":351000,"text":"it's a place where it's difficult, where you get disoriented,"},{"time":354000,"text":"maybe you get scared -- but you have to go through it"},{"time":357000,"text":"if you're going to get to some kind of deep reintegration."},{"time":360000,"text":"Then there should always be in sight the draw --"},{"time":364000,"text":"a kind of a beacon that draws you on through the labyrinth"},{"time":367000,"text":"to finish the process of getting there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370000,"text":"Now Brian Eno, who's been in the thick of the Long Now process,"},{"time":373000,"text":"spent two years making a C.D. called \"January 7003,\""},{"time":378000,"text":"and it's \"Bell Studies for the Clock of the Long Now.\""},{"time":381000,"text":"Based on -- parts of it are based on an algorithm that Danny Hillis developed,"},{"time":386000,"text":"so that a peal of 10 bells"},{"time":388000,"text":"makes a different peal every day for 10,000 years."},{"time":392000,"text":"The Hillis algorithm. 10 factorial gives you that number."},{"time":396000,"text":"And in fact, pretty soon we'll hear the sound."},{"time":399000,"text":"January 7003. There it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403000,"text":"OK, back to Danny's list."},{"time":405000,"text":"Number five of the seven is the payoff. This is it. The climax."},{"time":409000,"text":"The goal. The main thing that you're trying to get to."},{"time":413000,"text":"And then Danny says a really great journey will have a secret payoff."},{"time":417000,"text":"Something you didn't expect that caps what you did expect."},{"time":421000,"text":"Then there's the return."},{"time":423000,"text":"You've got to have a gradual return to the ordinary world,"},{"time":426000,"text":"so you have time to assimilate what you've learned. \n"},{"time":430000,"text":"And then, how about a memento? Number seven."},{"time":434000,"text":"At the end of it there's something physical,"},{"time":435000,"text":"a kind of reward that you take away."},{"time":437000,"text":"It might be a piece of a core drill of the mountain."},{"time":439000,"text":"Something that's just yours."},{"time":442000,"text":"How do you study a mountain"},{"time":445000,"text":"for the kinds of things we're talking about?"},{"time":447000,"text":"This is not a normal building project."},{"time":449000,"text":"What do you look for?"},{"time":450000,"text":"What are the elements that will most affect your ideas and decisions?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":456000,"text":"Start with borders. If you look on the left side of the cliffs here,"},{"time":459000,"text":"that's national park. That's sacrosanct --"},{"time":461000,"text":"you can't do anything with that. To the right of it is national forest."},{"time":464000,"text":"There's possibilities. The borders are important."},{"time":467000,"text":"Other elements were mines, weather, approaches and elevation."},{"time":475000,"text":"And especially trees. Look at those things up on top there."},{"time":478000,"text":"It turns out that Mount Washington is covered with bristlecone pines."},{"time":482000,"text":"They're the world's oldest living thing."},{"time":485000,"text":"People think they're just the size of shrubs, but that's not actually true."},{"time":490000,"text":"There are trees on that mountain that are 5,000 years old and still living."},{"time":497000,"text":"The wood is so solid it's like stone, and it lasts for a long time."},{"time":502000,"text":"So when you do tree ring studies of trunks that are on the mountain,"},{"time":506000,"text":"some of them go back 10,000 years."},{"time":509000,"text":"The stone itself is absolutely beautiful,"},{"time":511000,"text":"sculpted by millennia of very tough winters up there."},{"time":515000,"text":"We had tree ring analysts from the University of Arizona"},{"time":518000,"text":"join us on the expedition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520000,"text":"Now, if you guys have a pine cone handy,"},{"time":522000,"text":"now's a good time to put it in your hand and feel it, especially on the end."},{"time":527000,"text":"That's interesting."},{"time":529000,"text":"You'll find out why it's called a bristlecone pine. A little sensory experience. \n"},{"time":535000,"text":"Here's Danny Hillis in the midst of a bristlecone pine forest"},{"time":540000,"text":"on Long Now land. I should say that the age of bristlecones"},{"time":545000,"text":"was discovered, led by a theory."},{"time":548000,"text":"Edmund Schulman in the 1950s"},{"time":550000,"text":"had been studying trees under great stress at Timberline,"},{"time":554000,"text":"and came to the realization that he put in an article in Science magazine"},{"time":557000,"text":"called, \"Longevity under Adversity in Conifers.\""},{"time":563000,"text":"And then, based on that principle, he started looking around"},{"time":566000,"text":"at the various trees at Timberline,"},{"time":568000,"text":"and realized that the bristlecone pines --"},{"time":570000,"text":"he found some in the White Mountains that were over 4,000 years old."},{"time":575000,"text":"Longevity under adversity is a pretty interesting design principle in its own right. \n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":580000,"text":"OK, onto the mines. The first asking price for the property"},{"time":584000,"text":"when we looked at it in 1998 was one billion dollars for 180 acres and a couple of mines."},{"time":594000,"text":"Because the owner said, \"There's one billion dollars of beryllium in that mountain.\""},{"time":598000,"text":"And we said, \"Wow, that's great. Listen, we'll counter. How about zero?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":603000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":605000,"text":"And we're a non-profit foundation, you can give us the property"},{"time":609000,"text":"and take a hell of a tax deduction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":615000,"text":"All you have to do is prove to the government it's worth a billion dollars.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":618000,"text":"Well, a few years went by and there was some kind of back and forth,"},{"time":620000,"text":"and by and by, thanks to Mitch and Jay,"},{"time":622000,"text":"we were able to buy the whole property for 140,000 dollars."},{"time":627000,"text":"This is one of the mines. It doesn't have any beryllium in it."},{"time":631000,"text":"It's called the Pole Adit. And it does have tungsten,"},{"time":635000,"text":"a little bit of tungsten, left over, that's the kind of mine it was."},{"time":638000,"text":"But it goes a mile-and-a-half in a straight line,"},{"time":640000,"text":"due east into the range, into very interesting territory -- except that,"},{"time":646000,"text":"as you'll see when we go inside in a minute,"},{"time":649000,"text":"we were hoping for limestone but in there is just shale."},{"time":653000,"text":"And shale is not quite completely competent rock."},{"time":656000,"text":"Competent rock is rock that will hold itself up without any shoring."},{"time":660000,"text":"The shale would like some shoring,"},{"time":662000,"text":"and so parts of it are caved in in there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664000,"text":"That's Ben Roberts from -- he's the bat specialist from the National Park."},{"time":668000,"text":"But there are many wonders back in there, like this weird fungus"},{"time":672000,"text":"on some of the collapsed timbers."},{"time":674000,"text":"OK, here's another mine that's up on top of the property,"},{"time":678000,"text":"and it dates back to 1870."},{"time":680000,"text":"That's what the property was originally built around --"},{"time":682000,"text":"it was a set of mining claims. It was a very productive silver mine."},{"time":687000,"text":"In fact, it was the highest-operating mine in Nevada,"},{"time":690000,"text":"and it ran year round."},{"time":692000,"text":"You can imagine what it was like in the winter at 10,000 feet."},{"time":695000,"text":"You may recognize a couple of the miners there."},{"time":698000,"text":"There's Jeff Bezos on the right and Paul Saville on the left looking for galena, \n"},{"time":704000,"text":"which is the lead-silver thing. They didn't find any."},{"time":709000,"text":"They both kept their day jobs. Here's the last mine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714000,"text":"It's called the Bonanza Adit. It's down in a canyon."},{"time":716000,"text":"And Alexander Rose on the left there worked with a bunch of people"},{"time":720000,"text":"from the National Park to survey the whole mine. It's a mile deep."},{"time":723000,"text":"And they also found four species of bats in there."},{"time":726000,"text":"Now, almost all those mines, by the way, meet underneath the mountain."},{"time":730000,"text":"They don't quite, but it's something to think about."},{"time":733000,"text":"They don't quite meet."},{"time":735000,"text":"Let's go to weather. Mountains specialize in interesting weather."},{"time":741000,"text":"Way more interesting than Monterey even today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744000,"text":"And so one Tuesday morning last June, there we were."},{"time":747000,"text":"Woke up in the morning -- the mountain was covered with snow."},{"time":750000,"text":"That was a great time to go up and visit our weather station which again,"},{"time":754000,"text":"thanks to Mitch Kapor, we're building up there."},{"time":757000,"text":"And it's a pretty interesting scene."},{"time":760000,"text":"This is, on the left there, the joyful lady is Pat Irwin,"},{"time":763000,"text":"who's the regional head of the National Forest Service,"},{"time":766000,"text":"and they gave us the temporary use permit to be there."},{"time":770000,"text":"We want a temporary use permit for the clock, eventually --"},{"time":772000,"text":"10,000-year temporary use permit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":774000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":776000,"text":"The weather station's pretty interesting."},{"time":778000,"text":"Kurt Bollacker and Alexander Rose designed a radically wireless station."},{"time":782000,"text":"It runs on solar, and it sends a signal\nwith that antenna"},{"time":785000,"text":"and bounces it off of micrometeorite trails in the atmosphere"},{"time":791000,"text":"to a place in Bozeman, Montana, where the data is taken down"},{"time":795000,"text":"and then sent through landlines to San Francisco,"},{"time":798000,"text":"where we put the data in real time up on our website."},{"time":802000,"text":"And there you see a week of weather at 9,400 feet on Mount Washington."},{"time":808000,"text":"Let's go to approaches."},{"time":811000,"text":"As it happens, there are no trails anywhere on Mount Washington,"},{"time":815000,"text":"just a few old mining roads like this,"},{"time":817000,"text":"so you have to bushwhack everywhere."},{"time":818000,"text":"But there's no bears, and there's no poison oak,"},{"time":822000,"text":"and there's basically no people because this place has been empty for a long time. \n"},{"time":828000,"text":"You can hike for days and not encounter anybody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":831000,"text":"Well, here's a potential approach."},{"time":833000,"text":"You need to come up the Lincoln Canyon."},{"time":836000,"text":"It's this beautiful world all of its own, surrounded by cliffs,"},{"time":839000,"text":"and it's an easy hike to stroll up the canyon bottom,"},{"time":843000,"text":"until you get to this barrier, and it actually presents a problem."},{"time":850000,"text":"So you can scratch Lincoln Canyon as an approach."},{"time":855000,"text":"Another possible approach is right up the western front of the mountain."},{"time":858000,"text":"You can see why we sometimes call it Long Mountain."},{"time":861000,"text":"And from where you're standing at 6,000 feet in the valley,"},{"time":864000,"text":"it's an easy hike up to the mature pinyon and juniper forest"},{"time":867000,"text":"through that knoll at the front at 7,600 feet."},{"time":869000,"text":"And you can carry right on up through meadows"},{"time":872000,"text":"and steepening forest to the high base of the cliffs at 10,500 feet,"},{"time":877000,"text":"where there's a bit of a problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":880000,"text":"Now, Jeff Bezos advised us when he left at the end of the expedition,"},{"time":885000,"text":"\"Make the clock inaccessible."},{"time":889000,"text":"The harder it is to get to, the more people will value it.\""},{"time":893000,"text":"And check -- those are 600-foot vertical walls there."},{"time":898000,"text":"So Alexander Rose wanted to explore this route,"},{"time":903000,"text":"and he started over here on the left from his pickup truck"},{"time":907000,"text":"at 8,900 feet and headed up the mountain."},{"time":910000,"text":"Now, as you gain elevation your IQ goes down --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":914000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":916000,"text":"but your emotional affect goes up,"},{"time":918000,"text":"which is great for having a mythic experience,\n"},{"time":921000,"text":"whether you want to or not."},{"time":923000,"text":"In fact, Danny Hillis can estimate altitude"},{"time":926000,"text":"by how much math he can't do in his head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":929000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":932000,"text":"Now, I happened to be on the radio with Alexander"},{"time":934000,"text":"when he got to this point at the base of the cliffs, and he said, quote, \n"},{"time":939000,"text":"\"There's a hidden notch. I think I can get up a ways.\""},{"time":944000,"text":"Now, he's a rock climber, but you know, he's our executive director."},{"time":948000,"text":"I don't want him killed. I know he's going to love cliffs."},{"time":950000,"text":"I'm saying, \"Be careful, be careful, be careful.\""},{"time":953000,"text":"Then he starts going up, and the next thing I hear is,"},{"time":956000,"text":"\"I'm half-way up. It's like climbing stairs. I'm going up 60 degrees."},{"time":962000,"text":"It's a secret passage. It's like something from Tolkien.\""},{"time":966000,"text":"And I'm going, \"Careful, careful. Please be careful.\""},{"time":969000,"text":"And then, of course, the next thing I hear is,"},{"time":970000,"text":"\"I've made it to the top. You can see all of creation from up here.\""},{"time":973000,"text":"And he dashed across the top of the mountains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":976000,"text":"In fact, there he is. That's Alexander Rose."},{"time":978000,"text":"First ascent of the western face to Mount Washington,"},{"time":981000,"text":"and a solo ascent at that."},{"time":985000,"text":"This discovery changed everything about our sense of these cliffs"},{"time":988000,"text":"and what to do with them."},{"time":990000,"text":"We realized that we had to name this thing that Alexander discovered."},{"time":994000,"text":"How about Zander's Crevice? No."}]},{"cues":[{"time":998000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002000,"text":"So we finally decided on Alexander's Siq."},{"time":1005000,"text":"Zander's Siq is named after -- some of you have been to Petra,"},{"time":1008000,"text":"there's this wonderful slot canyon that leads into Petra"},{"time":1012000,"text":"called the Siq, and so this is the Siq."},{"time":1014000,"text":"And it really is hidden. I can't find it in this image,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"and I'm not sure you can."},{"time":1018000,"text":"Only when you get fresh snow can you see just along the rim there,"},{"time":1022000,"text":"and that brings it out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1024000,"text":"Now, Danny and I were up at this same area one day,"},{"time":1026000,"text":"and Danny looked over to the right"},{"time":1028000,"text":"and noticed something halfway up the cliffs,"},{"time":1031000,"text":"which is a kind of a porch or a cliff shelf with bristlecones on it,"},{"time":1035000,"text":"and supposed that people going up to the clock inside the mountain"},{"time":1039000,"text":"could come out onto that shelf and look down at the view."},{"time":1043000,"text":"And the people toiling up the mountain could see them,"},{"time":1046000,"text":"these tiny little people up there, incredibly halfway up the cliff."},{"time":1049000,"text":"How did they get there? Do I have to do that?"},{"time":1052000,"text":"And so that maybe becomes part of the draw and part of the labyrinth."},{"time":1055000,"text":"You can get another angle on Danny's porch"},{"time":1059000,"text":"by going around to the south and looking north at the whole formation there. \n"},{"time":1066000,"text":"And you need to know that Danny's clock is to be kept accurate"},{"time":1069000,"text":"by a ray of sunshine, that perfect noon hitting it every sunny day,"},{"time":1074000,"text":"and the pulse of heat from that sets off a solar trigger"},{"time":1077000,"text":"which resets the clock to make it perfectly accurate."},{"time":1080000,"text":"So even with the slowing of the rotation of the earth and so on,"},{"time":1082000,"text":"the clock will keep perfectly good time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1085000,"text":"So here we're looking from the south, look north."},{"time":1087000,"text":"This is all Forest Service land. If you go up on top of those cliffs,"},{"time":1091000,"text":"that's some of the Long Now land in those trees."},{"time":1094000,"text":"And if you go up there and look back, then you'll get a sense of"},{"time":1099000,"text":"what the view starts to be like from the top of the mountain."},{"time":1102000,"text":"That's the long view. That's 80 miles to the horizon."},{"time":1106000,"text":"And that's also timberline and those bristlecones really are shrubs."},{"time":1110000,"text":"That's a different place to be. It's 11,400 feet and it's exquisite."},{"time":1118000,"text":"Now, if you go over to the right from this image to looking at the edge of the cliffs,"},{"time":1122000,"text":"it's 600 foot, just about a yard to the left of Kurt Bollacker's foot,"},{"time":1126000,"text":"there is a 600-foot drop. He's ambling on over to Zander's Siq."},{"time":1131000,"text":"That's what it looks like looking down it."},{"time":1135000,"text":"We should probably put in a rail or something."},{"time":1139000,"text":"Over on the eastern side it's gentle, as you can see."},{"time":1143000,"text":"And that's not snow -- that's what the white limestone looks like."},{"time":1146000,"text":"You also see there a bighorn sheep."},{"time":1150000,"text":"Their herd was reintroduced from Wyoming."},{"time":1153000,"text":"And they're doing pretty well, but they've got a bit of trouble."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1156000,"text":"This is Danny Hillis, and he's figuring out a design problem."},{"time":1159000,"text":"he's trying to determine if where he is on a bit of Long Now land"},{"time":1164000,"text":"would appear from down in the valley to be the actual peak of the mountain."},{"time":1170000,"text":"because the real peak is hidden around the corner."},{"time":1172000,"text":"This is what in the infantry we used to call the military crest."},{"time":1176000,"text":"And as it turned out the answer is, yes,"},{"time":1179000,"text":"that is from down below in the valley it does look like the peak,"},{"time":1183000,"text":"and that might be conjured with."},{"time":1185000,"text":"We gradually realized we have three serious design domains to work on with this."},{"time":1190000,"text":"One is the experience of the mountain."},{"time":1192000,"text":"Another is the experience in the mountain."},{"time":1195000,"text":"And the third is the experience from the mountain,"},{"time":1198000,"text":"which is really dominated by the view shed"},{"time":1201000,"text":"of the spring valley there behind Danny,"},{"time":1205000,"text":"and if you look off to the right, out there,"},{"time":1207000,"text":"15 miles across to the Schell Creek range."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1211000,"text":"In the front, there are 10 ranches strung right along the base of the mountains"},{"time":1214000,"text":"using the water from the mountains."},{"time":1216000,"text":"In fact, there are artesian wells where water springs right into the air."},{"time":1221000,"text":"One of the ranches is called the Kirkeby Ranch,"},{"time":1224000,"text":"and I'll take you there for a minute."},{"time":1226000,"text":"It's a very nice ranch."},{"time":1228000,"text":"Alfalfa and cattle, run by Paul and Ronnie Brenham,"},{"time":1233000,"text":"and it's pretty idyllic. It's also hard work."},{"time":1238000,"text":"And most of these ranches are having trouble keeping going."},{"time":1240000,"text":"This is their view to the west of the Schell Creek range."},{"time":1244000,"text":"And if you go out to that line of trees at the far end,"},{"time":1247000,"text":"you'll see what the valley used to look like."},{"time":1251000,"text":"This is Rocky Mountain junipers that have been there for thousands of years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1256000,"text":"And a scheme emerged that Long Now is looking to see"},{"time":1259000,"text":"if it might be possible to buy up the whole valley,"},{"time":1262000,"text":"because those 10 ranches with their 17,000 acres"},{"time":1266000,"text":"dominate a 500 square mile valley with their grazing allotments and so on, \n"},{"time":1271000,"text":"and there's a possibility that you could get the whole thing"},{"time":1274000,"text":"for five million dollars and gradually restore it to its wild condition,"},{"time":1278000,"text":"and somewhere in the process turn it back over to the National Park,"},{"time":1282000,"text":"and it would double the size of Great Basin National Park. That would be swell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1286000,"text":"OK, let's take one more look at the mountain itself."},{"time":1289000,"text":"The clock experience should be profound,"},{"time":1293000,"text":"but from the outside it should be invisible."},{"time":1297000,"text":"Now, at the base of the high cliffs there's this natural cave."},{"time":1301000,"text":"It's only about 12 feet deep, but what if it were deepened from inside?"},{"time":1305000,"text":"You excavated from somewhere, came up from inside and deepened it."},{"time":1308000,"text":"And then you could have an entrance"},{"time":1309000,"text":"which was very rough and narrow as you first went in,"},{"time":1312000,"text":"that gradually becomes more refined and then actually quite exquisite."},{"time":1316000,"text":"And this stone takes a perfect polish."},{"time":1319000,"text":"You'd have a polished set of passages and chambers in there"},{"time":1324000,"text":"eventually leading to the 10,000 year clock."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1328000,"text":"And it's not a mine. This would be a nuanced evocation"},{"time":1332000,"text":"of the basic structure of the mountain,"},{"time":1335000,"text":"and you would be appreciating it as much from inside as you do from outside. \n"},{"time":1338000,"text":"This is architecture not made by building,"},{"time":1341000,"text":"but by what you very carefully take away."},{"time":1345000,"text":"So that's what the mountain taught us."},{"time":1348000,"text":"Most of the amazingness of the clock"},{"time":1351000,"text":"we can borrow from the amazingness of the mountain."},{"time":1355000,"text":"All we have to do is highlight its spectacular features and blend in with them."},{"time":1359000,"text":"It's not a clock in a mountain -- it's a mountain clock."},{"time":1364000,"text":"Now, the Tewa Indians in the Southwest have a saying"},{"time":1366000,"text":"for what you need to do when you want to think long term about anything."},{"time":1372000,"text":"They say, \"pin peya obe\" -- welcome to the mountain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1379000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1381000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}